# What I Hope to Learn
After years of being behind other industries, the cultural sector has not only broadly embraced the importance of data, but many organizations of varying sizes have made concerted efforts to collect and track audience, donor, and artist information. This shift has changed the way cultural organizations are making strategic marketing, fundraising, and programming decisions, but I would say there is still an analysis deficit in many artistic fields. In my experience, while arts managers may have had access to a significant amount of data, there is a lack of expertise regarding how to organize, interpret, and share the information it contains both internally and with external stakeholders. I hope that this course provides a thorough enough introduction to tools for data visualization so that my skillsets not only address this deficit and are more valuable to future employers, but so that these tools can be explained and introduced more broadly to the field.
